Introduction¶

Dataset Description¶

[ TMDb movie data] is adata collected about movies ,it has 21 columns which are(id,imdb_id, popularity, budget,revenue,original_title, cast, homepage, director, tagline, overview, runtime genres, production_companies,release_date, vote_count, vote_average,release_year,budget_ad,revenue_adj) here i will answer the questions: which genres are the most popular from year to year? what kinds of properties are associated with movies have high revenues?

    column_name=['revenue','budget','popularity','vote_count','vote_average','release_year']
    for c in column_name:
        df_highest_revs[c].mean(),df_low_revs[c].mean()
